'''Gerhard Gleirscher''' (born December 14, 1969) is an [[Austria]]n [[luge]]r who competed from 1990 to 2000. He won a complete set of medals at the [[FIL World Luge Championships]] with a gold in mixed team ([[FIL World Luge Championships 1997|1997]]), a silver in mixed team ([[FIL World Luge Championships 1991|1991]]) and a bronze in men's singles (1997).

Competing in three [[Winter Olympics]], Gleirscher also finished seventh in the men's doubles event in [[1992 Winter Olympics|1992]] and in the men's singles event both in [[1994 Winter Olympics|1994]] and in [[1998 Winter Olympics|1998]].

His best overall finish in the [[List of Luge World Cup champions|Luge World Cup]] was third in the men's singles in 1997-8.

